reviews.text: Old private estate shopping mall struggling to compete with new ones.  It is not the new huge malls with high ceilings big brands but you may like the surprises and the rare shops at the corners or far end of corridors.  There are a few shops selling expert model kits for adults and toys for teenagers and game console games also.
Many good restaurants, many hobby stores. Something for everyone. Best of all, affordable price.
Many delicious food such as Genki Sushi and Pizza Hut

A lot of choices to choose from, a cinema and stuff like that. What you would hope from a decent shopping mall. There are also housing estates above the shopping centre but ofc it's too expensive for a normal human being in Hong Kong to afford
Nice concentrated shops and diversity.

reviews.text:
A very welcome place to grab a light or hearty meal in the midst of the hustle and bustle of the city.

While plant-based / vegan is not too well known, the folks at Loving Hut are well versed, allowing for a safer place for those with dietary restrictions. 

The food is good for plant-based / vegans and non vegans alike.

It is a chained vegan fast food restaurant providing various kinds of Asian and Western food.  The place is quite large and clean.  The price is fair.  They have innovative food likes vegan egg made with bean curd sheet and vegan cheese.  Only cash and Octopus can be accepted for payment method.
With an innovative vegetarian menu and good cooking,  highly recommended.
Not a vegetarian but I love the vet roasted pock. It's good for ppl for seek for a healthier life.
It's quite delicious and efficient. They offer different options for vegetarians in hk, and the price is very acceptable.
